## Implement Item-Level Access Controls (Microsoft Fabric)

---

## 1ï¸âƒ£ Core Security Layers (EXAM FUNDAMENTAL)

Security is evaluated **top-down**:

```
Workspace access
   â†“
Item-level permissions
   â†“
Object-Level Security (OLS)
   â†“
Row-Level Security (RLS)
   â†“
Query result
```

âš ï¸ **If a user fails at any level, lower layers are never evaluated.**

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ Item-Level Access Control (What it REALLY means)

Item-level access controls:

* Determine **who can access an item**
* Apply to:

  * Lakehouses
  * Warehouses
  * Semantic models
  * Notebooks

âŒ They do **not**:

* Filter rows
* Hide columns

That is handled by **RLS / OLS**.

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Row-Level Security (RLS)

### Purpose

* Restrict **rows** returned to users
* Evaluated **at query time**
* Uses:

  * User identity
  * Group membership

---

### Where RLS Can Be Defined

| Location                       | Enforced For   | Exam Note                      |
| ------------------------------ | -------------- | ------------------------------ |
| **Semantic model**             | Power BI only  | âŒ Does NOT secure SQL endpoint |
| **Warehouse (SQL predicates)** | SQL + Power BI | âœ… Strongest enforcement        |

ğŸ“Œ **Exam rule:**

> â€œRegardless of access methodâ€ â†’ **Warehouse-level RLS**

---

### Typical Use Cases

* Region-based access
* Department-based filtering
* Multi-tenant reporting

---

## 4ï¸âƒ£ Object-Level Security (OLS)

### Purpose

* Hide:

  * Columns
  * Tables
* Does **not** filter rows

### Scope

* Defined in **semantic model**
* Applies to all Power BI access

---

### When to Use OLS

* Finance sees cost columns
* Sales does not
* Curated vs raw tables

---

## 5ï¸âƒ£ Workspace Roles vs Item Permissions

### Workspace Roles

| Role        | Purpose        |
| ----------- | -------------- |
| Admin       | Full control   |
| Member      | Edit content   |
| Contributor | Create content |
| Viewer      | Read-only      |

âš ï¸ Workspace roles:

* Control **visibility**
* Do **not** enforce data security

---

### Item Permissions

* Required before:

  * RLS
  * OLS
* If user cannot access item â†’ security rules never apply

---

## 6ï¸âƒ£ Lakehouse vs Warehouse Security (EXAM FAVORITE)

| Feature                    | Lakehouse    | Warehouse        |
| -------------------------- | ------------ | ---------------- |
| SQL GRANT                  | âŒ Limited    | âœ… Supported      |
| RLS                        | âŒ Data-layer | âœ… SQL predicates |
| Semantic model RLS         | âœ…            | âœ…                |
| Best for enforced security | âŒ            | âœ…                |

ğŸ“Œ **Rule:**
**Warehouse = stronger security boundary**

---

